docs.abstract: Residents of Key Haven, Fla, are protesting proposal by Florida Keys Mosquito Control District to use their tiny Key West suburb for first United States test of genetically-modified mosquitoes to blunt spread of Zika and dengue virus; will have to chance to vote in November referendum  on releasing altered bugs into their community; plan proponents say opposition is being led by science fiction instead of facts.
